VS Gaming recently signed a rights agreement with EA Sports to host a FIFA eWorld Cup Qualifier, which took place at Montecasino on 5-6 May 2018. 1,024 players competed for a prize pool of R1.5 million across PlayStation 4 and Xbox One, with the winners selected to represent South Africa at the Global Series Playoffs in August 2018. The number of competitors makes the VS Gaming FIFA 2018 tournament the largest FIFA gaming tournament on the continent. The prize pool for each platform was allocated as follows: The event also featured various activities and showcases, including VR gaming booths, PC hardware, interactive gaming setups, and live music performances. MyBroadband attended the VS Gaming FIFA 2018 tournament, with photos of the event below.                  